reviews.review_text: Delicious, fresh, local seafood - what more can you ask for! These guys are great. Ive picked up at their Fishermans Wharf location and one of their North Shore spots - both easy and high quality. They have an easy to use online platform, and a great selection.  I never buy seafood anywhere else!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for this review Anna, and we appreciate your ongoing support as a member! We are so happy to hear you love our wild and sustainable caught Canadian seafood selection!

reviews.review_text: We have ordered from Skipper Otto for 3 seasons now and absolutely love their products. We get our orders shipped to Ontario and have never had an issue, we love the quality, freshness, and value. We would definitely recommend Shipper Otto to all fish lovers out there. Keep up the great work guys! John & Virginia
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much John and Virginia! We so appreciate your support as members and so happy to hear you love our seafood!

reviews.review_text: Great location to buy fresh seafood, especially the spot prawns in May & June! They are not cheaper compared to the ones at the supermarkets, but you definitely get the freshest seafood of all! If you live in Vancouver, I recommend this place, why bother go all the way down to Steveston?
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the review Youngsung!

reviews.review_text: Excellent initiative. The staff are friendly and will do their best to accommodate requests.  Bought some fresh sustainably caught sockeye salmon and it tasted great!

Our family has been members of Skipper Otto for the last few years. The quality of the fish is amazing, it s convenient to order and pick up and the benefit to community and supporting small, local independent fishing families aligns with our values. Thanks for doing what you do!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Saul for this lovely review. We appreciate your support as a member and so happy to hear you are enjoying the seafood we provide directly from local independent fishing families in Canada.

reviews.review_text: Ive been a Skipper Ottos member for over 5 years. Love the ease of ordering online, and so many pickup locations for frozen items. Great selection of seafood too- scallops in the shell, albacore tuna, sablefish, lingcod cheeks, smoked salmon... A picture of the Fisherman who caught your seafood is on the package so you know exactly where it came from and can say a little thanks before eating. Fresh items is a Thursday evening pickup at Fishermans wharf- think spot prawns, mussels or live crab. Great business that I will continue to support.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Sheri for this review! We are so lucky to have you as a long time member, and so happy to hear you love our products and to know exactly how and when your seafood was caught by Canadian fishing families. Thank you for your continued support!

reviews.review_text: We have been members of Skipper Otto for several years.  The quality of the products are outstanding. Its easy to order online.  Its easy to do pick-ups at Fishermans Wharf and at community partners (e.g., Choices).  We believe in the way they do business: supporting local fishing families who catch seafood using sustainable methods.  Every time weve chatted with Skipper Otto staff, weve come away enriched by the conversation and full of admiration for their commitment to our oceans.

Ive been a member since their second year as a Community Supported Fishery. They have made many changes over the years to add more selection and make it easier to order/pick up. Every thing is delicious! But the best part is all the effort they put into educating their members about the fishing industry and the lives of the fishing families. I love the videos from the boats, the emails telling what to expect from the season, and updates when a salmon run doesnt open as expected.

Great quality, good feeling after supporting local and the staff is just beyond every expectation! Everything about Skipper Otto is great. Have been with them for two years and without hesitation I will sign up fro the next one... and hopefully many more to come! Thank you Skipper Otto! And  hoping you just keep introducing lesser known products - I am always in for that.

Been a member for a few years now. Its a great way to always have enough great tasting seafood on hand. Theres always staples (salmon, ling cod etc) available and then certain catches that are only around for a short while. Ideal sizes for 2 and 4 servings. Super easy to order and pick-up. Even better how it supports the fishermen/women directly.

This place is the BOMB. Sustainably caught seafood at a price that equitably covers the small business fishermen s wages. Their canned albacore tuna is a whole new experience of canned tuna - not tinny and fantastic real tuna taste! Sign up for the delicious seafood but stay for the recipe ideas, service and collective greater good

Love having access to fresh local fish all year round. The Fishermens Wharf is an easy place to pick up and to see what else is on the menu.  Skipper Ottos has an easy to use online platform.  Support your local fisherperson and join the Skipper Ottos community.
Sustainable, quality seafood and great support for the local fishing community. Ive never bought fish anywhere else since having Skipper Otto recommended to me. Plus, a great site!
Delicious fish caught by reputable fishermen. Great communication. Easy pick up at a store nearby. Whats not to like!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Shirley! Were so glad youve enjoyed being a member:)

reviews.review_text: I am very fortunate to know and be part of Skipper Otto! One regret is, I wish I could have known this amazing company like ten years ago! Love the quality of food, excellent customer service and reasonable price. Highly recommend.
Delicious, carefully prepared, sustainable seafood from fisher families - by purchasing from Skipper Otto, you re supporting small, family-owned businesses. Plus they have sushi-grade salmon!

Quality, selection and peace of mind for support local fishers is the best combination for putting nutritious and fresh food on my familys table.  Thank you Skipper Otto, you have never let us down!  :)
Community supported fisheries Sign up now to get in for next year!
If you are going to Granville island .. drop by the wharf
Skipper Otto is a place after my heart: local folk catching local seafood and serving local folk.  This is what fishing is all about.  This is what enjoying local is about.
Get your membership and join this great business. Regular prices but you have the guarantee youre getting sustainably obtained fresh fish, all while supporting a local, family business.
We love the fresh community supported seafood program.
Everything Ive bought here - different types of salmon, tuna, halibut, prawns, shrimp, oysters and mussels, all sustainable and ocean wise - has been absolutely delicious.
The best way to directly support the local fishing community AND eat great!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the review and kind words Eric - much appreciated. We are so happy to hear you love Skipper Otto and supporting our fishing families!

reviews.review_text: A phenomenal enterprise - a great Community Supported Fishery. Fresh fish, friendly people and passionate advocates for sustainable food practices.
If you want amazing seafood and help local fishermen you definitely need get your membership!
Super quality fresh seafoods,  membership required but its like you belong to a nice family with appreciation days, bbqs and get togethers.  Highly recommended
The fish is always amazing with Skipper Otto and I like knowing where it was caught and by whom.
Really convenient and fresh fish, never using the grocery store again
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Simon! We appreciate your support!

reviews.review_text: Spot prawns were awesome.  Easy purchase/pickup process too.
An excellent, sustainable, locally owned and operated seafood establishment. Highly recommended.
A remarkable business providing wonderful product with the lofty goal of changing the way the world consumes the fruits of its seas.
Amazing quality on sustainably caught seafood.
We love this membership, and the pickup is always friendly and painless
Join this place. Best seafood done right for the planet and our communities.
Fresh, tasty sustainable seafood that actually gives fishermen a fair share
Spend a day touring around, easy, many to see, street artists/singer. Two thumbs up
Always the freshest, most delicious seafood..
Great source for ultra fresh seafood.
Best fish in Vancouver from local fishermen
Great initiative and delicious seafood!

Have been a member several years. Super organized staff, seafood is great quality (and various price points to choose from), I just pick it up and pop it in my freezer. Online platform is great. Love picking up the fresh mussels (now that Ive learned how easy and fast they are to cook!). I rarely buy fish anywhere else and am glad to know it goes to local fisherman and works toward sustainable fisheries.

reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the 5 star rating Ian!
Thanks so much for the review and support Will - much appreciated!

reviews.review_text: I have ordered online. It s easy! The product is amazing.  The spot prawns are delicious.

Discovered this wonderful initiative recently. Have been happy with my membership. Support local fishermen who try to use sustainable methods. Get to know who is catching your seafood and how they catch it. Receive fresh, quality, in season seafood Get email reminders and notices on what is being caught and when theyll be out fishing. Get information on storing, handling and prepping the seafood.
Great local seafood but it is premium priced.
Best place to grab fish n chips in Vancouver!
Great fish coop
Community fishing produce sold here
Fresh seafood off the boats. Worth waiting for.
